{"id":"jealousy","term":"Jealousy","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Suspicion of a wife’s purity, one of the strongest passions (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 5:14\">Num. 5:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 6:34\">Prov. 6:34</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 8:6\">Cant. 8:6</a>); also an intense interest for another’s honour or prosperity (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 79:5\">Ps. 79:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Corinthians 10:22\">1 Cor. 10:22</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zechariah 1:14\">Zech. 1:14</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Numbers 5:14","Proverbs 6:34","Song of Solomon 8:6","Psalms 79:5","1 Corinthians 10:22","Zechariah 1:14"]}